ull,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make bleed"}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":["/fa.sˤa.da/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n33977","headword_ar":"فَصَدَ","root":"fSd","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) aor"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSodN","text_ar":"فَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiSaAdN","text_ar":"فِصَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, K,) [or the latter is a simple subst.,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K,) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K,) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AftSd","text_ar":"افتصد","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, * K.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSadahu","text_ar":"فَصَدَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSodN","text_ar":"فَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fiSaAdN","text_ar":"فِصَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (M, L,) or the latter is a simple subst., (Msb,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He cut,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"slit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it,"},{"kind":"text","text":"namely, a vein, (M, L.) [And app., accord. to"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2405},{"kind":"text","text":"the Msb,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He bled him by opening a vein;"},{"kind":"text","text":"agreeably with what here follows.] And one says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSada Aln~aAqapa","text_ar":"فَصَدَ النَّاقَةَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He slit"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opened"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a vein of the she-camel to draw forth the blood therefrom and to drink it"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to put it in a gut and broil it:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiydN","text_ar":"فَصِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (M L.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lamo yuHoramo mano fuSoda lahu","text_ar":"لَمْ يُحْرَمْ مَنْ فُصْدَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He has not been denied the entertainment of a guest for whom a camel has been bled by the slitting"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"opening"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a vein and who has had the blood so obtained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, A, * K,) is a prov.; (S, M, A, O;)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSoda","text_ar":"فُصْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"being for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuSida","text_ar":"فُصِدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, O, K,) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duroba","text_ar":"ضُرْبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Duriba","text_ar":"ضُرِبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qutola","text_ar":"قُتْلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qutila","text_ar":"قُتِلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (M;) and some, also, say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fuzoda","text_ar":"فُزْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, M, O, K;) for every quiescent"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"may be changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and every movent"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"S","text_ar":"ص"},{"kind":"text","text":"before"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"d","text_ar":"د"},{"kind":"text","text":"may have somewhat of the sound of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":"given to it, (S, M, O,) but may not in this case be altogether changed into"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"z","text_ar":"ز"},{"kind":"text","text":"; so that for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadara","text_ar":"صَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Sadafa","text_ar":"صَدَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"you may not say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zadara","text_ar":"زَدَرَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zadafa","text_ar":"زَدَفَ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (M:) some, also, say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano quSida lahu","text_ar":"مَنْ قُصِدَ لَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"q","text_ar":"ق"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mano A^uEoTiYa qaSodFA","text_ar":"مَنْ اُعْطِىَ قَصْدًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e. [who has been given] a little: (S, O, K:) the origin of the saying was this: two men passed the night at the abode of an Arab of the desert, and, meeting in the morning, one of them asked his companion respecting the entertainment given by the host, and the latter answered, “ I was not entertained as a guest, but only a vein [of a camel] was slit [or opened] to draw blood for me; ” whereupon the other replied in the words above: (O, K:) or a man used to entertain another as his guest in a time of scarcity, and, having no food to offer him, and being unwilling to slaughter his camel, bled it by slitting [or opening] a vein, and heated the blood that came forth, for his guest, until it became thick, and gave it to him to eat; and hence this prov.: (M, L:) it is applied to him who has obtained a part of that which he wanted. (Yaakoob, M, O, L, K.) [See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSiydN","text_ar":"فَصِيدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-  One says also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSada lahu EaTaA='F","text_ar":"فَصَدَ لَهُ عَطَا=ءً"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O, L, K,) aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faSodN","text_ar":"فَصْدٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (L,) meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He apportioned to him a gift,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stipend, and caused it to be transmitted to him."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, L, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","M","L","Msb"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}